Heliocentric redshift from HyperLeda. Note: a missing value represented with -1.0 does not imply that no redshift exists
Mean surface brightness within D25_LEDA based on the brightness in MAG_LEDA
Approximate brightness (Note: this magnitude estimate is heterogeneous in both bandpass and aperture but for most galaxies it is measured in the B-band within D25_LEDA ; use with care)

Approximate group diameter. For groups with a single galaxy this quantity equals D25_LEDA. For galaxies with multiple members we estimate the diameter of the group as the maximum separation of all the pairs of group members (plus their D25_LEDA diameter)

Major axis diameter measured at the mu=26 mag arcsec-2 r-band isophote based on SMA_SB26. If the r-band surface-brightness profile could not be measured at this level the diameter is set equal to 2.5 x SMA_SB25 or 1.5 x D25_LEDA in that order of priority
Galaxy position angle measured positive clockwise from North as measured from the ellipse moments (or equivalent to PA_LEDA if the ellipse moments could not be measured)
Minor-to-major axis ratio as measured from the ellipse moments (or equivalent to BA_LEDA if the ellipse moments could not be measured)

Second moment of the light distribution along the major axis based on the measured ellipse moments (-1 if not measured). Equivalent to MAJORAXIS (but converted to arcsec) in the Ellipse Fits table (https://www.legacysurvey.org/sga/sga2020/#ellipse-fits)

For a 5-sigma point source detection limit in r, flux (in nanomaggies) = 5/((psfdepth_r)^0.5). And flux (in AB magnitude) = -2.5*[log10(5/((psfdepth_r)^0.5))-9].
For a 5-sigma point source detection limit in W1, flux (in nanomaggies) = 5/((psfdepth_w1)^0.5). And flux (in AB magnitude) = -2.5*[log10(5/((psfdepth_w1)^0.5))-9].
For a 5-sigma point source detection limit in W2, flux (in nanomaggies) = 5/((psfdepth_w2)^0.5). And flux (in AB magnitude) = -2.5*[log10(5/((psfdepth_w2)^0.5))-9].
For a 5-sigma point source detection limit in W3, flux (in nanomaggies) = 5/((psfdepth_w3)^0.5). And flux (in AB magnitude) = -2.5*[log10(5/((psfdepth_w3)^0.5))-9].
For a 5-sigma point source detection limit in W4, flux (in nanomaggies) = 5/((psfdepth_w4)^0.5). And flux (in AB magnitude) = -2.5*[log10(5/((psfdepth_w4)^0.5))-9].
For a 5-sigma point source detection limit in z, flux (in nanomaggies) = 5/((psfdepth_z)^0.5). And flux (in AB magnitude) = -2.5*[log10(5/((psfdepth_z)^0.5))-9].
